The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Makelele, Thuram bid adieu
                                                                                                                                                                                                     EURO DIARY
                      
	Makelele, Thuram bid adieu  
	Zurich: France midfielder Claude Makelele and defender Lilian Thuram bid adieu to their international career after Tuesdays 0-2 loss to Italy.  
	I always said that this was my last competition I think the new generation must work, and stick together. And I am behind them all the way, Makelele, who plays for Chelsea said.         
	After this elimination, I am ending my career with the France team, Thuram said.         
	Loew decision         
	Basel: Germany coach Joachim Loew has been banned from the touchline for Thursdays quarter final with Portugal after being sent off in their last group B match, the German football federation (DFB) said on Wednesday.         
	Igor to sit out         
	Bad Tatzmannsdorf: Croatia striker Igor Budan will miss the rest of Euro 2008 with a knee injury, coach Slaven Bilic said on Wednesday.                                                                                                                                    
